Name: NAPHTHA (PETROLEUM ETHER)
Reference: Whiticar, S. Bobra, M., Fingas, M., Jokuty, P., Liuzzo, P., Callaghan, S., Ackerman, F., and Coa, J. 1992. A Catalogue of Crude Oil and Oil Product Properties (1992 Edition). Prepared for Environment Canada, EE-144, Ottawa, Ontario. 643pp.
Alternate names: benzin, benzine, petroleum benzin, canadol, light ligroin, Skellysolve
Comments: For this product the upper flammability limit is 5.9% and the lower flammability limit is 1.1%. This material contains primarily pentane and iso-hexane, no aromatics. Also known as benzin, benzine, petroleum benzin, canadol, light ligroin, and Skellysolve, per Anonymous, 'EnviroTIPS: Naphtha", Environmental and Technical Information for Problem Spills Manual, Technical Services Branch, Environmental Protection Directorate, Environmental Protection Service, Environment Canada, Cat. No. En 48-10/43-1985E (1985).
Notes: The version of this record in EE-125 has more data than this ADIOS record does.
